2. cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) - The paper discusses restricted classes of context-free grammars and their properties, which is a core topic in formal languages and automata theory. 
3. cs.LG (Learning) - The paper mentions linear grammars, which are a type of formal language that can be used for machine learning tasks. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the computational complexity of detecting disentailment for the GRAMMAR constraint, which is a problem in algorithms and data structures. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper's focus on grammars and constraints could be relevant to the development of AI systems that can understand and generate natural language.
